{
    "problem": "If $\\displaystyle{f(x)=x^{(x+1)}(x+2)^{(x+3)}}$, then find the value of $f(0)+f(-1)+f(-2)+f(-3)$.",
    "level": "Level 5",
    "type": "Algebra",
    "solution": "Since  $0^z=0$ for any $z>0,\\ f(0) =f(-2)= 0$. Since $(-1)^0=1$, \\begin{align*}\nf(0)+f(-1)+f(-2)+f(-3)&=(-1)^0(1)^2+(-3)^{-2}(-1)^0 \\\\\n&=1+\\frac{1}{(-3)^2} = \\boxed{\\frac{10}{9}}.\n\\end{align*}"
}